@afchung @markusweimer I pushed new version.I tried testing only with Local runtime or only with Yarn and it does not work (works only with both) as avro types are not nullable by default and you need union types to represent nullable types. I tried changing it to union types but apparently c# avro for nullable types is not readable by java side. For example it produces:

{"sharedAppSubmissionParameters":{"tcpBeginPort":8900,"tcpRangeCount":1000,"tcpTryCount":1000},"localRuntimeAppParameters":{"sharedAppSubmissionParameters":{"tcpBeginPort":8900,"tcpRangeCount":1000,"tcpTryCount":1000},"maxNumberOfConcurrentEvaluators":2},"yarnRuntimeAppParameters":null,"defaultRuntimeName":"Local","runtimes":["Local"]}

When the expected is:
{"sharedAppSubmissionParameters":{"tcpBeginPort":8900,"tcpRangeCount":1000,"tcpTryCount":1000},
"localRuntimeAppParameters":{"org.apache.reef.reef.bridge.client.avro.AvroYarnAppSubmissionParameters":{"sharedAppSubmissionParameters":{"tcpBeginPort":8900,"tcpRangeCount":1000,"tcpTryCount":1000}},"maxNumberOfConcurrentEvaluators":2},
"yarnRuntimeAppParameters":null,"defaultRuntimeName":"Local","runtimes":["Local"]}

Any ideas?
